OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Len Trewin
OL,5,F"A piece of shrapnel (hit my
OL,6,Fforehead). We were marching along the
OL,7,Froad and they were firing 20mm cannons
OL,8,Fdown the road like machine guns - and
OL,9,Fbursting shells. It's still there.
OL,10,FThere was no way to get any help.
OL,12,F"The worst thing I saw was a mortar
OL,13,Fbomb dropped amongst three officers
OL,14,Fand two of them had their legs blown
OL,15,Foff. I was here and they were.... And
OL,16,FI thought to myself 'that's your lucky
OL,17,Fday, mate.'
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/5
