OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Len Trewin
OL,5,F"The thing I remember most was all the
OL,6,Fmarching. Because being a parachute
OL,7,Fbattalion, we had no transport. Well,
OL,8,Fthe only transport was feet."
OL,10,FThe battalion returned to England
OL,11,Fbefore later being sent to the
OL,12,FArdennes in north eastern France.
OL,14,F"It's something that had to be done
OL,15,Fand you had no say in it," Mr Trewin
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,F"It's fading now, dying out -
OL,19,Fmemories. You remember friends that
OL,20,Fwas killed."
